This paper is about the analysis of the joint probability distribution of hidden variables in different layers of a fully connected deep network, which is a topic that falls under the broad category of machine learning and neural networks. Specifically, the paper focuses on the effect of the activation function on this distribution. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.IT (Information Theory). Additionally, the paper involves mathematical analysis and convergence results, which could also place it in the sub-categories of cs.SI (Systems and Control) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
